Inconsistent with the rest of the chronology in the stratigraphy

The maximum age of this sample is not consistent with its stratigraphic position and therefore the entire Acheulean assemblage from layers 6-8 have been bracketed by minimum date of 1.07ma, and pooled age given above.

One radiocarbon date is available for this layer, but it is attributed to horizons B and D in different publications (horizons B, C and D correlate to Nivel 3 and Nivel 4). We chose to assign it to layer D based on Urquijo, 2004. Another date of 44 ka is often mentioned in the literature but no lab results are provided and therefore this date is not used.

column9: Tektites were unearthed at Baigu site (another Palaeolithic site in Bose Basin) in 1993 from the laterite deposit of T4, the same laterite deposit (Layer 3) as that of Fengshuling. According to the Ar/Ar dating of tektites from Baigu (Hou et al., 2000), the age of layer 3 should be approximately 803 kya.

Tektites were unearthed at Baigu site (another Palaeolithic site in Bose Basin) in 1993 from the laterite deposit of T4, the same laterite deposit (Layer 9) as that of Gaolingpo. According to the Ar/Ar dating of tektites from Baigu (Hou et al., 2000), the age of layer 9 should be approximately 803 kya. It is inferred that the age of layers below layer 9 should be equal to or, more likely, older than 803 kya.

traditionally, PaD was seen as part of the Anglian Glaciation (MIS 12). Lee et al. 2006 date PaD to MIS 17 due to its stratigraphical position between the Happisburgh Formation (MIS 16) and the periglacial structures on the Cromer Forest-bed Formation, dated to MIS 18. An alternative hypothesis dates it to MIS 15

According to Shen et al. 2004, the Layer 3 composed of limestone breccia was most probably resulting from cryoclastic activities during an ice age, and Layer 4 of reddish soft sandy clay, presumably accumulated during a warm and humid period. In this regard, Layer 4 might be older than ZSW-5 (284,000 yr) by one glacial–interglacial cycle on the SPECMAP time scale (Winograd et al., 1997). This assigns an age of ca. 400,000 yr to the lower strata of this site.
